# StoneCore — Handcrafted Zen Decor

## Project Overview
StoneCore is an e-commerce website for handcrafted Zen decor products including stone gardens, miniature shrines, bonsai arrangements, and meditation accessories. The website features a dynamic product catalog powered by PHP and MySQL.

## Folder Structure

stonecore/
├── config.php ← Database connection
├── database.sql ← Import in phpMyAdmin
├── products-loader.js ← Add to index.html
├── api/
│ ├── products.php ← GET all products
│ ├── add_product.php ← POST add product
│ ├── edit_product.php ← POST edit product
│ └── delete_product.php ← GET delete product
├── admin/
│ └── index.html ← Admin panel
├── css/
│ └── styles.css ← Main stylesheet
├── js/
│ └── ProductsLoader.js ← Product loader script
├── img/ ← Product images folder
└── index.html ← Main website


## Prerequisites
- XAMPP / WAMP / MAMP (PHP 7.4+ and MySQL)
- Web browser (Chrome/Firefox recommended)

## Step 1 — Database Setup
1. Start XAMPP and turn on **Apache** and **MySQL** services
2. Open phpMyAdmin: `http://localhost/phpmyadmin`
3. Click on **New** database or import directly
4. Click **Import** tab
5. Choose the `database.sql` file from the project folder
6. Click **Go** at the bottom
7. Database `stonecore_db` will be created with sample product data

## Step 2 — Config Update
Open `config.php` and update your database credentials:

```php
<?php
// config.php — Database Connection

define('DB_HOST', 'localhost');
define('DB_USER', 'root');           // Change if your username is different
define('DB_PASS', '');               // Add your MySQL password if any
define('DB_NAME', 'stonecore_db');

$conn = new mysqli(DB_HOST, DB_USER, DB_PASS, DB_NAME);

if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die(json_encode([
        'success' => false,
        'message' => 'Connection failed: ' . $conn->connect_error
    ]));
}

$conn->set_charset('utf8mb4');
?>

Step 3 — Project Location
Move the entire stonecore folder to your web server directory:

XAMPP: C:/xampp/htdocs/stonecore/

WAMP: C:/wamp/www/stonecore/

MAMP: /Applications/MAMP/htdocs/stonecore/

Step 4 — Frontend Connection
Make sure index.html includes the product loader script. Add this line just before the </body> tag:

html
<script src="products-loader.js"></script>
If the script is in a js/ folder, use:

html
<script src="js/ProductsLoader.js"></script>
Step 5 — Admin Panel Access
Open your browser and navigate to:

text
http://localhost/stonecore/admin/
From the admin panel you can:

View all products

Add new products

Edit existing products

Delete products

Step 6 — View Website
Open your browser and go to:

text
http://localhost/stonecore/
API Endpoints
Method	URL	Description
GET	http://localhost/stonecore/api/products.php	Get all products
POST	http://localhost/stonecore/api/add_product.php	Add a new product
POST	http://localhost/stonecore/api/edit_product.php	Edit existing product
GET	http://localhost/stonecore/api/delete_product.php?id=1	Delete product by ID
API Response Examples
GET /api/products.php
json
{
  "success": true,
  "products": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Product 1",
      "category": "Zen Stack",
      "price": "1499.00",
      "description": "Handcrafted stacked river stones...",
      "image": "img/Image1.png",
      "created_at": "2025-01-15 10:30:00"
    }
  ]
}
POST /api/add_product.php (Form Data)
Field	Type	Required
name	string	Yes
category	string	Yes
price	decimal	Yes
description	string	No
image	file	No
GET /api/delete_product.php?id=1
json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Product deleted"
}
Troubleshooting
Database Connection Error
Make sure MySQL is running in XAMPP

Check username/password in config.php

Verify database name stonecore_db exists

Products Not Loading on Website
Check browser console for errors (F12 → Console tab)

Verify products-loader.js path is correct

Make sure api/products.php returns JSON data

Image Upload Fails
Ensure img/ folder has write permissions (755 on Linux/Mac)

Maximum file size: 2MB

Allowed formats: JPG, JPEG, PNG, WEBP

404 Errors
Make sure project is inside htdocs folder

URL should be http://localhost/stonecore/ not file:///...

